    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-02-06T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-02-06T14:00:00-05:00" n="206"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d206">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/1391: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative of the President</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-02-06T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 6, 1939—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. With reference to my telegram No. 15 dated February 3, 6 p.m., Zúñiga
                    Montúfar and I discussed the advisability of having the note referred to therein
                    delivered in person by Ocheltree acting for the Permanent Secretariat. I am
                    inclined to favor this as he could informally explain the technical features of
                    the matter with a view to allaying Honduran objections to the aerial
                    reconnaissance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
